Maintainer: Karim Oualkacha <oualkacha.karim@uqam.ca>
Description: This is a unified copula-based framework which tests for secondary phenotypes association and a single SNP in presence of selection bias. The method fits both retrospective and prosepctive likelihoods to handel selection bias under case-contro (CC), extreme-trait (ET) and mulitple-trait (MT) sampling designs. The dependence between primary and secondary phenotypes is modelled via copulas. Thus, SPAC is a robust method for non-normality assumptiom of the secondary trait.
Depends: R (>= 3.2.2), MASS, LaplacesDemon, VineCopula, copula
Imports: MASS, CompQuadForm, Matrix, mvtnorm, mnormt, numDeriv, VineCopula, copula
Suggests: knitr, methods
